      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, the differences are all minor, but they\u0027re a result of doing the modulation in the vertex shader. The old code converted the float coverage to a byte, then did integer math to modulate the GrColor by that value. The new code sends the color in as a uniform, and the coverage as a float attribute, so there\u0027s less quantization happening.",
      "parentUuid": "c2088353_fb344930",
